{:title "Add Artifact Persistence Integration Tests"
 :description
 "The artifact persistence bug (fix-artifact-persistence.spec.edn) was fixed in
  commits 57a0c29 and 7f93a14, which corrected phase handoff paths and added
  handoff_test.clj. However, the original spec called for comprehensive integration
  tests that validate actual filesystem persistence and failure modes. These were
  not created. This spec covers only the missing test tasks.

  What exists:
  - handoff_test.clj: validates artifact data flows between phases in-memory
  - verify_test.clj: basic verify phase tests

  What's missing:
  - Integration tests that validate files are written to disk
  - Failure-mode tests for empty artifacts, zero files written, success=false
  - Phase-level unit tests for implement/release artifact validation

  When done, push a PR for review."

 :intent
 {:type :test
  :scope ["components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/artifact_persistence_test.clj"
          "components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/verify_test.clj"
          "components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/release_test.clj"]}

 :constraints
 ["Test-only change — no production code modifications"
  "Tests must validate actual filesystem changes (use temp dirs)"
  "Mock LLM/agent calls but exercise real phase and release-executor code paths"
  "Follow existing test patterns: deftest, testing, with-redefs, is with messages"
  "All existing tests must continue to pass (bb test)"
  "Pre-commit hooks must pass on final commit"
  "Push a PR to GitHub when tests are green"]

 :workflow/type :standard-sdlc
 :workflow/version "2.0.0"

 :plan/tasks
 [{:task/id :create-persistence-integration-tests
   :task/description
   "Create: components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/artifact_persistence_test.clj

    Read first to understand patterns:
    - components/workflow/test/ai/miniforge/workflow/handoff_test.clj (context setup, mocking)
    - components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj (what release does)
    - components/release-executor/src/ai/miniforge/release_executor/core.clj (file writing)
    - components/release-executor/src/ai/miniforge/release_executor/files.clj (write-and-stage-files!)

    Tests to create:

    1. test-release-writes-files-to-disk
       - Create a temp directory
       - Build a context with a mock implement result containing :code/files
       - Execute release phase (or release-executor directly) against temp dir
       - Assert files physically exist on filesystem
       - Assert file contents match what was in the artifact
       - Assert metrics show :files-written > 0
       - Clean up temp dir

    2. test-release-creates-parent-directories
       - Artifact contains files in nested paths (e.g. src/ai/miniforge/foo/bar.clj)
       - Assert parent directories are created automatically
       - Assert files exist at correct nested paths

    3. test-release-handles-file-actions
       - Test :create action — file is created
       - Test :modify action — existing file is overwritten
       - Test :delete action — existing file is removed
       - Each action verified on filesystem

    4. test-release-fails-with-empty-artifact
       - Context has implement result with {:code/files []}
       - Release should either fail or report :files-written 0
       - Workflow should not silently succeed

    5. test-workflow-fails-when-success-false
       - Mock a phase to return {:status :failure :success false}
       - Verify workflow runner propagates the failure
       - Error message should include which phase failed"
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies []}

  {:task/id :add-release-phase-unit-tests
   :task/description
   "Create or extend: components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/release_test.clj

    Read first:
    - components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/release.clj
    - components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/verify_test.clj (for test patterns)

    Tests to add:

    1. test-release-extracts-artifact-from-context
       - Build context with implement result at expected path
       - Assert release phase finds and uses the artifact

    2. test-release-returns-files-written-metrics
       - Mock release-executor to return known metrics
       - Assert release phase result includes :files-written count

    3. test-release-handles-missing-implement-result
       - Context has no :implement in :execution/phase-results
       - Assert release phase produces a clear error, not NPE"
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies []}

  {:task/id :add-verify-phase-artifact-tests
   :task/description
   "Extend: components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/verify_test.clj

    Read first:
    - components/phase/src/ai/miniforge/phase/verify.clj (how it reads artifact)
    - components/phase/test/ai/miniforge/phase/verify_test.clj (existing tests)

    Tests to add:

    1. test-verify-reads-artifact-from-implement-result
       - Build context with implement result containing code artifact
       - Assert verify phase extracts code and passes it to tester agent

    2. test-verify-handles-missing-artifact-gracefully
       - Context has implement result with no :output
       - Assert verify phase behavior (fail or fallback, document which)"
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies []}

  {:task/id :run-tests-and-push-pr
   :task/description
   "Validate and ship:
    1. Run bb test — all tests must pass (existing + new)
    2. Run bb pre-commit — must pass
    3. Create branch: test/artifact-persistence-integration
    4. Commit with message: 'test(persistence): add integration tests for artifact filesystem persistence'
    5. Push branch and create PR targeting main
    6. PR title: 'test(persistence): add artifact persistence integration tests'
    7. PR body should list the new test files and what each test validates"
   :task/type :test
   :task/dependencies [:create-persistence-integration-tests
                       :add-release-phase-unit-tests
                       :add-verify-phase-artifact-tests]}]}
